          "INC-SOURCE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "incident_source": [
                  "SPALL"
                ],
                "reaction": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " Spallation reaction in a mercury target",
                "irradiated with 3-GeV protons (600 kW) .",
                "The proton beams were supplied at a repetition rate of",
                "25 Hz and in the \"double-bunch mode\".",
                "Produced neutrons were slowed down in a supercritical",
                "para hydrogen moderator.",
                "A Cd filter was used to cut the low-energy tail of",
                "neutron pulse.",
                "To reduce gamma-rays from a large 14.4 eV s-wave",
                "resonance, an enriched Xe-131 (84.4%) gas filter",
                "with a pressure of 0.43 MPa, and a thickness of 76 mm",
                "was installed upstream of the Xe-131 sample."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "INC-SPECT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Relative neutron flux was reconstructed using the 478",
                "keV gamma-rays from gamma rays from the B-10 (n,alpha",
                "gamma) Li-7 reactions."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GE",
                "BGO"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " An array of Ge detector consists of two",
                "cluster-Ge detectors and eight coaxial-Ge detectors",
                "with BGO anti-coincidence shields.",
                "DAQ: CAEN V1724 Digitizer (14bit, 100MHz)"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "84.4% enriched Xe-131 gas sealed into a cylindrical",
                "cell with a pressure of 0.43 MPa, a diameter of 49 mm",
                "and a thickness of 76 mm."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Flight length: 21.5 m"
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Dead time correction was applied with a paralyzable",
                "dead time model."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "SHAPE"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " The resonance parameters of the 3.2-eV p-wave",
                "resonance were determined by fitting the relative",
                "gamma yeild gated with the full absorption and single",
                "escape peaks of 7132 keV gamma rays. The 3.2-eV",
                "p-wave resonance was fitted with the Breit-Wigner",
                "function including the background and the s-wave",
                "component (1/v term) . The effects of the Doppler",
                "broadening (free gas at 295 K) and the resolution",
                "function of ANNRI were convolved with the",
                "Breit-Wigner function. In the fitting, the total",
                "width of the 3.2-eV p-wave resonance was used as the",
                "gamma width, because the neutron width of the p-wave",
                "resonance is negligibly smaller than the gamma width."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ERR-ANALYS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": {
                "heading": "DATA-ERR",
                "minimum_value": null,
                "maximum_value": null,
                "correlation_property": null
              },
              "free_text": [
                " The uncertainty of resonance prameters",
                "were deduced from the uncertainty of the fitting",
                "result."
              ]
            }
          ],
